[Term]
id: CHEBI:5623
name: harman
namespace: chebi_ontology
def: "An indole alkaloid fundamental parent with a structure of 9<em>H</em>-β-carboline carrying a methyl substituent at C-1. It has been isolated from the bark of <em>Sickingia rubra</em>, <em>Symplocus racemosa</em>, <em>Passiflora incarnata</em>, <em>Peganum harmala</em>, <em>Banisteriopsis caapi</em> and <em>Tribulus terrestris</em>, as well as from tobacco smoke. It is a specific, reversible inhibitor of monoamine oxidase A." []
