namespace: chebi_ontology
def: "A proanthocyanidin consisting of (−)-epicatechin and (+)-catechin units joined by a bond between positions 4 and 8' respectively  in a β-configuration.. Procyanidin B1 can be found in <em>Cinnamomum verum</em> (Ceylon cinnamon, in the rind, bark or cortex), in <em>Uncaria guianensis</em> (cat's claw, in the root), and in <em>Vitis vinifera</em> (common grape vine, in the leaf) or in peach." []
